  "why": "The paper applies mutations as image-level transformations (pixel-level: contrast/brightness; affine: translation/scaling/rotation; texture: blurring/stylizing) and uses a validity check referenced to pixel intensities on the 0–255 scale (is_valid uses a threshold β × 255). This indicates mutations are performed on raw input pixel values rather than in a latent/embedding space, and the authors enforce simple bounds on pixel change magnitudes. However, the paper does not describe explicit handling of serialization constraints (e.g., rounding to integer precision, explicit clipping/rounding when saving to standard image formats, or experiments verifying that failures persist after saving/serialization), nor does it discuss conversion/rounding of generative-model floating tensors into serialized formats. Because the work mutates raw input values and partially enforces pixel-range constraints but does not explicitly ensure or demonstrate that perturbations survive denormalization/serialization, the appropriate rating is Medium.",
